This paper deals with the problem of estimating the number of unique identifiers in data streams, which is a common problem in database systems and data mining. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms for solving this problem, which involves data structures and algorithms for processing data streams, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions variance bounds and sampling algorithms, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses tradeoffs between accuracy, space usage, and update speed, which is a common theme in algorithm design and analysis (cs.AL).
